Well it's me again:Hi Paul &amp; Cook,I am already seen as a nutcase and even am scheduled by social security for a mental evaluation.They just don't get it,I am tired and after having over 100+ tumors cut out by the VA and then them tell me that all I can do is go home and die,I cannot say that I do not think of how much eaiser it would be for me,however there are greater things than me,I have a truly wonderful wife and family,and if I think of my pain then the pain with this cancer is nothing compared to the pain any actions I would take for relief.You remember how it was when we would go into a village and Pray that we didn't have to kill a child,I remember quite well and the stress I felt knowing just how possible it was to happen.I thank each of YOU out there,those who see and those who even think me wrong,it is truly my belief that WE who served in any war/conflict have given to provide a country where even the most controverseial?can speak,I do listen to even the Jane Fonda's of this world because after all,arren't we all seeking the TRUTH!! I said I listen,not agree,but by listening WE can get many views and opinions.It is my desire that WE can keep the dialog moving and try our best to be honest and allow the views and opinions of others to enter into a debate that is respectful.The pool is a problem and our contractor is learning about not keeping his word,my wife is on his case and I believe the 2nd.Armor Div.sent her their Hell On Wheels Patch.May GOD smile upon you and those you love.Outlaw 11,Daniel/Charlotte Knight&amp;Family
